Every mother thinks she knows best and it seems that seals are no different.

New research has found that grey seals have distinctly different personalities which results in individual ways of mothering their young.

Researchers from Durham University and the University of St Andrews have found that seal mothers adopt a wide variety of mothering styles when caring for their pups. 

